<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no" ?>
<FinalDraft DocumentType="Script" Template="No" Version="1">
  <Content>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>INSTIGATOR</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Written by</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>MadBrad Smith</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE IN:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>1. EXT. ROCCO'S TAVERN – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Rain falls across a quiet Chicago block. Neon flickers above the door: ROCCO'S TAVERN.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Shouting erupts from inside.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>2. INT. ROCCO'S TAVERN – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Two BAR SECURITY GUARDS struggle to separate TERRY and JARRETT, both regulars, swinging wildly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Patrons scatter while others record with their phones. The door opens. DETECTIVE BRANDON FINNEY steps inside, soaked from the rain.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Alright. That's enough.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney wedges between them while</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>security restrains the fighters.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Take a breath. Both of you.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Now tell me why you started fighting.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>TERRY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I don't know.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JARRETT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>He swung at me.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Before that. What happened before the swing?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JARRETT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Nothing. He just looked at me.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>BARTENDER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>It's just Jarrett and Terry. They're regulars.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>BARTENDER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>No clue what got into them tonight.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney studies their confusion carefully.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>3. EXT. STREET ACROSS FROM ROCCO'S – SAME TIME</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Across the street stands DR. LENA VOSS under an awning. She watches the fight through the window.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>In her hand: a notebook labeled INSTIGATOR.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She writes observations calmly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>4. INT. LATE NIGHT GROCERY STORE – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Fluorescent lights buzz overhead. The store is quiet. LENA finishes bagging her groceries at the checkout area. The sliding doors open. FINNEY enters grabs a bottle of juice and gets into line.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Two strangers argue nearby. Their voices escalate quickly. A shove. A punch. The fight begins.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Hey! Break it up!</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney separates them while startled shoppers back away.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You know each other?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FIRST MAN</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>No.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>SECOND MAN</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Never seen him before.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Then why'd you swing?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>SECOND MAN</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I don't know. I just got</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>mad.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Across the store Lena watches the altercation like a scientist observing data.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She finishes scanning and walks out calmly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>5. INT. CPD DISTRICT – BULLPEN – LATE NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney pins two reports onto a corkboard: ROCCO'S TAVERN and GROCERY STORE.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Two strangers. Two fights. Same answer.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>He writes a word on the whiteboard: TRIGGER.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>6. INT. CAPTAIN THOMAS' OFFICE – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CAPTAIN THOMAS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Two guys fighting in a bar.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Two guys fighting in a grocery store.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Why is this on my desk?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Because neither of them knows why it started.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Something's pushing these situations.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CAPTAIN THOMAS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Fine. Look into it. Quietly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>7. EXT. BUS STOP – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A city bus stops. Lena steps off. The bus pulls away. She walks toward a WOMEN'S SHELTER building.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>8. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>STAFF MEMBER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Morning, Dr. Voss.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Morning.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>9. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – HALLWAY – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Residents move through the hallway starting their day. KIARA waits outside Lena's office door. Anxious.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena walks down the hallway carrying a folder.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You got a minute?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Sure.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She opens the office door.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Come on in.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>10. INT. LENA'S OFFICE – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Tell me what happened before the argument.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>He said something stupid.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>What did he say?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>That I should be grateful just to be here.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena writes: TRIGGER —</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>DISRESPECT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>11. INT. POLICE STATION – FRONT DESK – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>SGT NOLEN</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Morning, gentlemen.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>MORALES</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Morning, Sarge. That your real hair?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CARTER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>We're trying to figure out if it's police issued.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>SGT NOLEN</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Go before you get written up.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>MORALES</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>It would totaly be worth it.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The two officers walk away laughing down the hallway.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>12. INT. SQUAD ROOM – ROLL CALL – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Officers sit around the room as the meeting is already in progress. A few officers joke quietly in the back.Laughter spreads through the room.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CAPTAIN THOMAS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Alright, alright — settle down.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>We've had a few unusual altercations around the city.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>If anyone sees anything unusual, forward it to Detective Finney.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>13. INT. VIDEO REVIEW ROOM – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>FINNEY and DETECTIVE JORDAN PARK review surveillance footage from ROCCO'S TAVERN.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You want the outside camera?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Yeah. Run it.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The footage reveals Lena standing across the street watching the bar.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Who's that?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>No idea.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>14. INT. VIDEO REVIEW ROOM – LATER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Now the grocery store footage. Jordan zooms in on Lena scanning groceries.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Hold on... that's the same girl from the other video.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Yeah.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney studies the screen carefully.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>15. INT. CITY BUS – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A nearly empty city bus rattles through the streets. Lena sits halfway back, quietly observing the passengers. Two strangers sit across from each other. A tense silence builds. Lena casually speaks while looking at her phone.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Some people think staring is disrespectful.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>One man glances at the other. The tension rises.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>PASSENGER 1</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You got a problem?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>PASSENGER 2</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You talking to me?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The argument escalates quickly. Voices rise. Suddenly the men stand. A fight erupts in the aisle. Passengers shout. The bus driver slams the brakes. Lena stands calmly and moves toward the exit.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>16. EXT. CITY BUS STOP – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The bus doors open. Lena steps off onto the sidewalk. Behind her the fight ontinues inside the bus. Lena walks away into the night, expression calm, almost satisfied.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>17. INT. CPD DISTRICT – BULLPEN – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The bullpen buzzes with the start of a new shift. Detective FINNEY stands at a whiteboard covered with reports, times, and locations. Photos from Rocco's Tavern and the grocery store are pinned side by side.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Same night. Same kind of escalation. DETECTIVE JORDAN PARK studies</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>the board.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Coincidence?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Doesn't feel like one.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney circles a photo of Lena from the surveillance footage.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>18. INT. VIDEO REVIEW ROOM – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>More surveillance footage plays across multiple monitors. Park scrubs through timestamps from nearby cameras.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You think she's somehow starting these?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I think she's there every time they happen.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Park freezes another frame showing Lena leaving the grocery store.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>That's not normal behavior.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>19. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Residents move through the halls. Volunteers organize supplies. LENA walks calmly through the environment, observing everything. KIARA sits in the common area, tense and withdrawn. WALTER BRIGGS, a stocky man in work clothes, organizes boxes in a supply room doorway nearby. Lena notices the distance between them. She studies their body language.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>20. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – HALLWAY – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Residents move through the hallway starting their day. KIARA waits outside Lena's office door. Anxious. Lena walks down the hallway carrying a folder.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You got a minute?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Sure.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She opens the office door.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Come on in.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>21. INT. LENA'S OFFICE – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena sits with Kiara again. Her notebook rests open.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>How have things been since yesterday?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Same. People around here talk like they know me.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Disrespect can feel constant in shared spaces.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Kiara nods slowly, processing that thought.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>22. INT. CPD DISTRICT – RECORDS ROOM – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney flips through city incident reports. Minor altercations. Disturbance calls. Street fights. He starts placing new locations on a city map.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>There are more.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Park looks over his shoulder.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>How many?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Enough to notice a pattern.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>23. EXT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney's car idles across the street. He watches people entering and leaving the building. Through the windshield he sees Lena exiting the shelter briefly to take a phone call. Finney studies her carefully.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>24. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – SUPPLY ROOM AREA – LATE AFTERNOON Walter Briggs moves boxes through the hallway. Kiara walks past him without making eye contact. The tension between them is noticeable. From down the hallway, Lena quietly observes the interaction. She makes a small note in her notebook.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>25. EXT. CITY STREET – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney drives through Chicago traffic thinking through the case. The skyline glows as the sun sets. He glances again at a printed photo of Lena.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Who are you?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>26. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Residents settle in for the evening. Lena moves through the hall like she belongs to the routine. She pauses outside the supply room where Briggs works late. Across the hall, Kiara sits alone with headphones on. Lena watches both of them quietly — considering something. A slow realization forms in her expression. She closes her notebook. The experiment continues.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>27. EXT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Morning traffic passes on the street. Residents enter and leave the building.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Across the street, FINNEY sits in his car watching the shelter entrance.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A coffee sits untouched in the cup holder as he studies the flow of people.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>28. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – COMMON AREA – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Residents sit around tables. A TV murmurs in the background. KIARA scrolls through her phone, clearly irritated about something. WALTER BRIGGS carries boxes from the supply room toward a storage closet. LENA enters the room quietly, observing both of them. She notices Kiara glance up at Briggs with obvious tension.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>29. INT. SUPPLY ROOM – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Shelves filled with donated clothes and supplies. Briggs organizes boxes, muttering to himself while working. Lena appears in the doorway.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Walter, do you have a minute?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>BRIGGS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Sure, Doc. What's up?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Just checking in. You've been working a lot of late shifts.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>BRIGGS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Someone's gotta keep this place running.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena nods thoughtfully.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Some residents have been</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>saying they feel judged when people stare at them.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>BRIGGS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I don't stare at anybody.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I'm sure you don't mean anything by it.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She makes a note in her notebook.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>30. INT. HALLWAY – MOMENTS LATER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Kiara walks down the hall toward the common area. Lena intercepts her casually.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>How are you feeling today?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Same as always. People around here think they're better than me.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>That must be frustrating.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Kiara nods.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Sometimes people don't realize how disrespectful they seem.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Kiara glances toward the supply room where Briggs is working.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>31. EXT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney watches from his parked car. Through the windshield he sees Lena walking through the building interior window. He studies her movements carefully.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>What are you doing in there?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>32. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – SUPPLY ROOM AREA – LATE AFTERNOON Briggs carries a box into the hallway. Kiara walks past him again. Their shoulders almost bump.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>BRIGGS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Watch it.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Excuse me?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>BRIGGS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You heard me. Some of us are trying to work.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The tension rises immediately.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You think you're better than everybody here?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>BRIGGS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I didn't say that.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You didn't have to.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Residents nearby begin to watch the argument.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>33. INT. HALLWAY – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena stands at the far end of the hallway, quietly observing the escalation.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She writes one word in her notebook: TRIGGER.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>34. INT. SUPPLY ROOM AREA – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The argument intensifies.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>BRIGGS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Look, I'm just trying to do my job.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Yeah? Then stop looking at me like I'm trash.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Briggs steps closer.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>BRIGGS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Nobody said that.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're saying it right now.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Suddenly Kiara shoves him. Briggs stumbles backward into a</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>stack of boxes. Other residents scream.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>35. EXT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – SAME TIME</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney hears the shouting from inside the building. He looks toward the entrance, alert.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>36. INT. SHELTER HALLWAY – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The fight continues briefly as staff rush in to separate them. Lena calmly closes her notebook. Her expression reveals nothing. Another experiment complete.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>37. EXT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – LATE AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney steps out of his car as shouting echoes from inside the building.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Two patrol officers arrive at the same time.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>OFFICER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You hear that?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Yeah. Let's go.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>38. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – HALLWAY – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Residents crowd the hallway as staff try to separate KIARA and WALTER BRIGGS.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Boxes are knocked over. Clothes spill across the floor.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Alright, break it up!</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney helps pull the two apart while the officers hold them back.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Everyone calm down. Nobody's helping by yelling.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Kiara is furious. Briggs is defensive but shaken.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>What happened here?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>He disrespected me.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>BRIGGS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>That's not what happened. She shoved me first.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney studies both of them carefully. The same confusion he's seen before.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>39. INT. SHELTER OFFICE AREA – MOMENTS LATER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney takes quick notes while a staff member explains the situation.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>STAFF MEMBER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Arguments happen sometimes, but it usually doesn't escalate like that.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Has it happened before?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>STAFF MEMBER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Not like this.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney nods slowly, thinking.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>40. INT. SHELTER HALLWAY – SAME TIME</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>At the end of the hall, Lena watches the aftermath quietly. Finney notices her standing there observing the scene. For a moment their eyes meet.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>41. INT. SHELTER OFFICE – MOMENTS LATER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney speaks with Lena for the first time.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You work here?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Yes. I'm one of the</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>counselors. Dr. Lena Voss.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney nods politely, writing the name down in his notebook.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You see what started the argument?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Just the end of it. Voices raised, then the push.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Her tone is calm and professional. Completely believable.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Seems like people are getting angry pretty fast lately.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Stress does that to people. Especially in environments like this.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney studies her for a moment. Something about her composure stands out.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>42. EXT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The patrol car pulls away with Briggs for questioning. Residents slowly return inside. The commotion fades. Finney stands beside his car reviewing notes from the incident. He glances back toward the shelter entrance.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>43. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – LENA'S OFFICE – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena sits alone writing in her notebook. On the page: TRIGGER: DISRESPECT ESCALATION WINDOW: IMMEDIATE RESULT: PHYSICAL CONFLICT She underlines the final line. Another observation logged.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>44. EXT. CITY STREET – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney drives through the city, deep in thought. Streetlights streak across the windshield.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>It's not random.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>He grips the steering wheel, replaying the events in his head. Across town, Lena continues writing in her notebook. Two different minds studying the</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>same phenomenon — for very different reasons.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>45. INT. CPD DISTRICT – BULLPEN – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney stands in front of his investigation board. Photos, maps, and incident reports cover the wall. Multiple altercations across the city are pinned with colored markers. At the center of the board is a photo of LENA VOSS from surveillance footage.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>That's a lot of fights for coincidence.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Exactly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney connects two more locations with a red marker.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Every one of them escalates the same way. Fast. Personal.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>46. INT. VIDEO REVIEW ROOM – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>More surveillance footage rolls across the monitor. Park scrolls through timestamps from multiple nearby cameras.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's not starting them. She's just… there.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Maybe being there is the point.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Park pauses the footage showing Lena entering the shelter building earlier that day.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You already met her.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Yeah. Counselor at the shelter.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney watches the screen again. Thinking.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>47. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Residents move through the common area. Lena walks calmly through the environment, observing interactions around her. Two residents argue quietly at a table before separating. Lena notices the tension but keeps walking.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>48. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – HALLWAY – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Residents move through the hallway starting their day. KIARA waits outside Lena's office door. Anxious. Lena walks down the hallway carrying a folder.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You got a minute?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Sure.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She opens the office door.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Come on in.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>49. INT. LENA'S OFFICE – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena writes in her notebook again. Pages filled with behavioral observations.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>NOTES:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>TRIGGER: PERCEIVED DISRESPECT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>ESCALATION SPEED: HIGH</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>OUTCOME: PHYSICAL CONFLICT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She flips to a new page.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>TITLE: GROUP ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>50. INT. CPD DISTRICT – CAPTAIN THOMAS' OFFICE – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney stands across from CAPTAIN THOMAS.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CAPTAIN THOMAS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're telling me someone's out there starting fights?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I'm saying they're being pushed.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CAPTAIN THOMAS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>By a counselor?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I'm not saying that yet.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Thomas studies the board photos on the desk.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CAPTAIN THOMAS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Then what are you saying?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I'm saying I need more time.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>51. EXT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney's car sits across the street again. He watches Lena exit the building with several residents. She laughs with them — perfectly normal. Finney studies her carefully.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You don't look like someone starting fights.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>52. INT. CITY BUS – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena rides quietly, notebook in her bag this time. Two passengers argue softly near the front of the bus. Lena notices. Watches. But this time she does nothing. The argument fades away. No escalation. Lena looks almost disappointed.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>53. INT. FINNEY'S CAR – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney reviews printed surveillance photos under the dome light. Each one shows Lena somewhere near an altercation. He places them side by side across the passenger seat.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You show up a lot.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>54. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Minimalist apartment. Clean. Quiet.Lena sits at a small desk reviewing her notebook. She draws a diagram connecting emotional triggers to behavioral responses. At the top of the page she writes one word:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>INSTIGATION.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She circles it slowly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>55. INT. CPD DISTRICT – BULLPEN – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney studies the investigation board again. More altercation reports are pinned across the map. Lena's photo sits in the center like the eye of a storm.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're staring at that picture like it's going to confess.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I'm waiting for it to make sense.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney studies timestamps from several incidents.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Every one of these happens within minutes of her arrival.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>56. INT. VIDEO REVIEW ROOM – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Multiple camera feeds play across monitors. Park rewinds one of the incidents frame by frame.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You think she's pushing people somehow?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Maybe not pushing.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Maybe nudging.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Park looks at him skeptically.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>That's a new one. Criminal nudging.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>57. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – COMMON AREA – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Residents gather around a table playing cards. Lena walks past slowly, observing interactions. Two residents begin arguing quietly over the game. Lena pauses nearby. Listening.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>RESIDENT 1</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You always cheat.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>RESIDENT 2</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I'm not cheating. You're just losing.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The tension grows. Lena leans slightly closer, speaking casually as if to</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>herself.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>People get defensive when they feel embarrassed. The comment lands. The argument intensifies immediately.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>58. INT. CPD DISTRICT – RECORDS ROOM – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney flips through stacks of disturbance reports. Street fights. Bar fights. Domestic disputes. He highlights several dates.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>It's spreading.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>59. EXT. COFFEE SHOP – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney sits at an outdoor table across the street from the shelter.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>He watches Lena exit the building again. She stops to talk with a resident outside. Laughing easily. Finney watches carefully.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're either the luckiest witness in Chicago…</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Or something else.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>60. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The apartment is quiet and minimalist. Lena studies her notebook at a desk.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Charts connect emotional triggers to behavioral outcomes. She writes:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>VARIABLE: GROUP DYNAMICS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Below it:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>ESCALATION PROBABILITY INCREASES WITH AUDIENCE SIZE</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She closes the notebook slowly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>61. EXT. CITY STREET – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney walks alone along the sidewalk outside a bar district. Crowds gather outside multiple bars. He studies how easily arguments begin in crowded spaces. A drunk patron bumps another man accidentally. Finney watches closely. Waiting to see if it escalates. But the men laugh it off and walk away.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>So what's the difference?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>62. INT. CITY BUS – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena rides quietly again. Two passengers argue softly near the front. Lena watches them carefully. This time she says nothing. She simply observes the</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>tension fade. Her notebook remains closed in her bag. Even without interference, the system reveals its patterns.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>63. INT. CPD DISTRICT – BULLPEN – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney studies the investigation wall again. The board has grown — more incidents, more locations. Every line seems to circle back to one photograph: DR. LENA VOSS.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>This is getting bigger than random fights.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Yeah. Someone's turning up the temperature.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney pins another incident report onto the board.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>64. INT. CAPTAIN THOMAS' OFFICE – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney stands across from Captain Thomas again.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CAPTAIN THOMAS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're still chasing that counselor?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I'm chasing a pattern.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CAPTAIN THOMAS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Then prove it.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney nods. That's exactly what</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>he intends to do.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>65. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena studies a page in her notebook labeled:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>GROUP</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>ESCALATION THRESHOLD.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Charts connect emotional triggers with environmental factors. She writes a new variable:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>PUBLIC CROWD + ALCOHOL + STATUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CONFLICT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She circles it slowly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>66. EXT. SPORTS BAR DISTRICT – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A busy Chicago nightlife strip packed with fans leaving a game. Crowds spill out of multiple bars. Music, shouting, laughter everywhere.Lena walks through the crowd calmly, observing. Two groups of fans bump into each other accidentally. The tension is there — but it hasn't exploded yet. Lena pauses nearby.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Funny how people get brave in crowds.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>One of the men hears it. Looks at the other group again.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FAN 1</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You got something to say?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FAN 2</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You talking to us?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The tension spikes instantly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>67. EXT. SAME STREET – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The argument grows louder. A shove. Then another. Within seconds multiple people are involved. A bar fight spills into the street. Lena steps back into the crowd watching calmly. Police sirens approach in the distance.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>68. EXT. BAR DISTRICT – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney arrives with responding officers. The crowd scatters as police break up the fight.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>OFFICER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Started out of nowhere.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney scans the crowd instinctively. Across the street he briefly spots Lena disappearing into the crowd.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Hey—!</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's already gone.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>69. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – LATE NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena writes calmly in her notebook.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>ENTRY:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>ENVIRONMENT: PUBLIC CROWD</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>TRIGGER: STATUS CHALLENGE</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>RESULT: MULTIPLE PARTICIPANTS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She pauses, thinking. Then writes one final line:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>ESCALATION SCALE: SUCCESSFUL</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>70. INT. CPD DISTRICT – BULLPEN – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney stares at the investigation wall. Incidents cover half the room. In the center: photos of Lena Voss from different locations.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're obsessed.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I'm close.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney grabs a photo of Lena leaving the subway station.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's planning something bigger.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>71. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena studies her notebook. A new page reads:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>CONTROLLED ESCALATION ENVIRONMENT. Below it:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CROWD SIZE – MODERATE</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>STATUS COMPETITION – HIGH</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>ALCOHOL – OPTIONAL</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She circles one location on a city map.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>72. INT. LIVE MUSIC BAR – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A packed neighborhood venue. Music. Drinks. Tight space. Finney enters quietly, scanning the crowd. Across the room — Lena sits alone at a table.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney freezes. This time he doesn't lose her.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>73. INT. LIVE MUSIC BAR – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Two men stand near the bar arguing over who ordered first. The tension is mild — not yet dangerous. Lena watches them closely. Finney watches Lena.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>People hate feeling invisible. One of the men hears it.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>MAN 1</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>What did you say?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The other man smirks.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>MAN 2</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Maybe he was talking about you.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The tension spikes instantly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>74. INT. BAR FLOOR – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The argument grows louder. A shove. Drinks spill. A crowd forms quickly. Finney pushes through the crowd trying to reach Lena.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Hey! Break it up!</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>But the fight is already happening.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>75. INT. BAR TABLE AREA – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney reaches Lena. She watches the chaos calmly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You knew that would happen.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena finally turns to him.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Did I?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You said one sentence.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>And they went after eachother.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena studies him with curiosity.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>That's interesting.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>76. EXT. BAR – LATER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Police cars break up the fight outside. Finney exits the bar, furious. Lena walks out moments later.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're not the observer.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're the instigator.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena smiles slightly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're the first person who's noticed.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney stares at her.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're playing with people.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I'm studying them.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>77. EXT. CITY STREET – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena walks away into the crowd. Finney watches her disappear. For the first time, he knows exactly what she is. But proving it will be something else entirely.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>78. INT. CPD DISTRICT – BULLPEN – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney pins a new photo of Lena to the board. The wall now looks like a psychological crime map.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>So now you know she's doing it.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Yeah.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Can you prove it?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney stares at the board. The answer is obvious.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Not yet.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>79. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena studies a new notebook page labeled:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>DETECTIVE VARIABLES.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Under it she writes:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>SUBJECT: BRANDON FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>OBSERVATION: PATTERN RECOGNITION</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>HIGH</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She smiles slightly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Let's see how predictable you are.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>80. EXT. STREET FOOD MARKET – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A crowded street market filled with food vendors and music. Finney walks through the crowd after receiving a disturbance call. Across the plaza Lena stands watching from a distance. Two customers argue about cutting in line.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena casually speaks while looking at a menu board.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>People hate when someone thinks they're more important. The tension spikes immediately.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUSTOMER 1</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You think you're special?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUSTOMER 2</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Say that again.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The argument explodes into a fight.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney rushes forward to break it up.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>81. EXT. MARKET EDGE – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney separates the fighters. Across the crowd Lena watches him work. She's not studying the fight anymore. She's studying him.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>82. INT. COFFEE SHOP – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney sits reviewing incident reports. Lena enters quietly and orders coffee.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Two customers nearby argue about a laptop charger. Lena glances at Finney before speaking.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Some people take things that don't belong to them.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The comment lands between the arguing customers. The argument escalates  instantly. Finney looks up — and sees Lena watching him.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're doing it again.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Am I?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>83. EXT. CITY STREET – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney catches up to Lena outside the café.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're staging situations now.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>No.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I'm observing how you respond to them.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're manipulating people.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're manipulating</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>investigations.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>They stand face-to-face under a streetlight.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Someone's going to get seriously hurt.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>People are always hurting each other.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I'm just revealing how easy it is.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>84. INT. FINNEY'S CAR – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney sits in silence after the encounter. Photos of incidents cover the passenger seat. He writes one word across the top of a new page:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>INSTIGATOR.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Then underneath:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>DR. LENA VOSS.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney knows the game now. And Lena knows he's playing.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>85. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Sunlight cuts through the blinds. Lena studies a wall filled with behavioral diagrams. Clusters of incidents are circled across a map of Chicago. A new page in her notebook reads: SYSTEM STRESS TEST.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>If pressure increases… what breaks first?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>86. EXT. CITY PARK – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A busy lunchtime crowd fills the park. Office workers sit at tables. Kids run through fountains. Lena watches quietly from a bench. Two joggers collide near a food cart.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JOGGER 1</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Watch where you're going.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JOGGER 2</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Maybe slow down.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The tension builds. Lena says nothing this time. The argument fizzles out. She makes a note.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>RESULT: NO ESCALATION WITHOUT NUDGE.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>87. INT. FINNEY'S CAR – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney studies photos spread across the passenger seat. Every photo shows Lena near a disturbance.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're evolving the experiment.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>88. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Residents gather for dinner. Kiara laughs with another resident. Lena observes quietly from across the room. Two residents argue about seating.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Funny how people protect territory.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The argument grows louder. Staff intervene before it becomes violent.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena writes: ESCALATION PARTIAL.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>89. INT. FINNEY'S APARTMENT – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A modest apartment. Files and photos cover the kitchen table. Finney studies Lena's timeline while drinking cold coffee.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Three environments. Three outcomes.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>What's the next variable?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>90. EXT. COMMUTER BUS STOP – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Crowds wait for buses during rush hour. Lena stands in line with commuters.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Two strangers argue about someone cutting ahead.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lines make people feel powerless.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The comment spreads through the line. Several commuters begin shouting.  Security arrives before a fight breaks out. Lena quietly leaves the line.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>91. INT. CPD VIDEO REVIEW ROOM – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Park rewinds footage from the bus stop.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>That's her again.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Yeah.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney leans closer to the screen.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's not picking random places.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's testing environments.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>92. EXT. ROOFTOP BAR – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A stylish rooftop bar overlooking the city skyline. Lena sits alone with a drink observing groups nearby. Two coworkers argue about promotions.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Recognition matters more than money sometimes.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The insult lands. The argument escalates instantly.A drink is thrown. Security moves in. Lena watches calmly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>93. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Residents begin their day. Walter Briggs stocks shelves in the supply room.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Kiara passes him without speaking. The tension remains from the earlier fight.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena observes from the hallway.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>94. EXT. BUSY INTERSECTION – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Traffic backs up after a minor fender bender. Drivers shout from their cars. Lena stands on the sidewalk nearby.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>People hate feeling blamed.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Two drivers step out and begin yelling. A crowd forms quickly. Police arrive before punches land.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>95. INT. CPD DISTRICT – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney pins three new incidents onto the board. Park studies the pattern.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's accelerating.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Yeah.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's getting closer to something bigger.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>96. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – LATE NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena reviews the week's experiments. She writes one final line in the notebook.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>NEXT PHASE: SYSTEM FAILURE.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She looks out the window at the city lights. Chicago is her laboratory.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>97. EXT. ROOFTOP OVERLOOK – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena stands above the city watching traffic move like arteries of light. Her notebook rests open on the ledge. Dozens of incidents now fill the pages.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Phase five begins.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>98. INT. CPD DISTRICT – INCIDENT BOARD ROOM – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney and Park study a massive digital map of Chicago. Multiple disturbances blink across the screen.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>They're spreading faster now.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Because she doesn't need to start them anymore.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Now the system feeds itself.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>99. INT. NEIGHBORHOOD GROCERY STORE – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena walks slowly through the aisles. Two customers argue over the last carton of eggs.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Scarcity makes people irrational.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Within seconds the argument escalates. A manager rushes in. Lena exits calmly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>100. EXT. PARKING LOT – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney arrives just as the argument spills outside. He looks around — Lena is gone again.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's staying one step ahead.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>101. INT. CITY BUS DEPOT – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Drivers complain about delays and long routes. Lena listens quietly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>When systems fail, people blame each other.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Two drivers begin shouting about scheduling. A supervisor intervenes. Lena records the outcome.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>102. INT. FINNEY'S CAR – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney studies dozens of incident reports. He begins circling a specific downtown district.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're funneling everything toward one place.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>103. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Residents eat dinner quietly. The atmosphere is tense. Kiara watches Lena carefully now.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You like watching people argue.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I like understanding why.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Kiara looks unsettled.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>104. INT. TRAIN PLATFORM – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Crowds wait for a delayed train. Announcements echo through the station.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Frustration spreads quickly. Lena whispers one sentence to a commuter.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>They don't respect your time.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Passengers begin shouting at transit staff. Security arrives. Lena blends into the departing crowd.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>105. INT. CPD COMMAND CENTER – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney watches a city map lighting up with disturbances.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's synchronizing them.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>For what?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A cascade.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>106. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – MIDNIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The wall map now shows a dense cluster of red marks. Nearly every one converges on the same downtown grid. Lena writes the next line in her notebook.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINAL PHASE – TOTAL SYSTEM STRESS.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She looks out over Chicago. The city hums with tension.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Let's see how strong you really are.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>107. INT. CPD DISTRICT – BULLPEN – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney's board now covers nearly the entire wall. Dozens of incidents connected by red lines. In the center: LENA VOSS.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>This is getting out of control.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>That's the point.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney circles three incidents from the previous night.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's scaling it up.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>108. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena studies a map of downtown Chicago.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Crowd flow diagrams fill her notebook.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She writes:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>VARIABLE: HIGH DENSITY PUBLIC EVENT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Below it:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>POTENTIAL ESCALATION – EXPONENTIAL</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>109.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>EXT. CITY STREET FESTIVAL – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A massive outdoor festival fills several city blocks. Food trucks, music stages, hundreds of people. Police patrol casually through the crowd.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney moves through the festival searching. He knows Lena will be here somewhere.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>110. EXT. FESTIVAL SIDE STREET – SAME TIME</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena stands near a food truck line observing the crowd. Two groups argue about someone cutting the line. The tension is mild. Not enough yet. Lena steps closer.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Funny how fast people get angry when they think someone's cheating them.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The line erupts immediately.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>111. EXT. FESTIVAL STREET – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The argument spreads through the crowd. People start shouting. A shove turns into a fight. Then another. Within seconds multiple groups are involved.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>112. EXT. FESTIVAL MAIN STREET – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney pushes through the chaos. Police begin breaking up fights. Festival security scrambles.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Break it up! Move back!</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>He scans the crowd desperately. Across the street — Lena watches calmly again.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>113. EXT. FESTIVAL EDGE – MOMENTS LATER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney finally reaches her.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You just turned a nice calm festival into a riot.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I said one sentence.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You knew what it would do.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>So did you.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>They stare at each other as sirens echo through the festival.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>114. EXT. FESTIVAL STREET – LATER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Police lights flash across the scene. Several people are injured. Ambulances arrive.Finney watches the aftermath.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>This stops now.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You can't stop human behavior, Detective. You can only observe it.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>115. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena writes calmly in her notebook.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>ENTRY: LARGE SCALE ENVIRONMENT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>RESULT: CASCADE ESCALATION SUCCESSFUL</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She pauses, thinking. Then writes another note.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>VARIABLE: DETECTIVE INTERFERENCE</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena smiles slightly. The experiment just got more interesting.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>116. INT. LOCAL NEWSROOM – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Televisions display reports about rising disturbances across Chicago. A NEWS ANCHOR speaks about 'unexplained altercations spreading across the city.'</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>In the background, LENA watches the broadcast from a visitor chair, unnoticed.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She writes in her notebook:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>MEDIA AWARENESS – NEW VARIABLE.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>117. EXT. DOWNTOWN PLAZA – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lunch crowds fill the plaza. Finney watches people moving through the square. Two street musicians argue over space.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's testing density.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>He calls Park.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's about to try something bigger. I can feel it.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>118. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Maps now show clusters of incidents across several blocks. Lena connects three locations with a red marker. She writes:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CASCADE START POINTS.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Three circles appear across the downtown map.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>119. INT. CITY BUS GARAGE – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Drivers prepare for their routes. Lena sits in the break area observing conversations. Two drivers argue about scheduling.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>People take delays personally.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The argument spikes instantly before a supervisor interrupts. Lena leaves quietly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>120. INT. CPD DISTRICT HALLWAY – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney walks quickly past officers responding to new disturbance calls. Park catches up.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Three fights in twenty minutes.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Same pattern?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Same timing.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney realizes something.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's not starting one fight.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's starting several.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>121. EXT. RIVERWALK – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Crowds stroll along the riverwalk bars and restaurants. Lena stands by the railing watching three different groups nearby. She makes a brief comment to each as she walks past.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Funny how people hate being disrespected in public. Minutes later — three separate arguments begin along the walkway. Security rushes in as shouting</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>spreads through the crowd. Lena disappears into the night.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>122. INT. FINNEY'S KITCHEN – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney studies incident reports while coffee brews. He places three locations on a map. Each occurred within minutes of the others.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>It's happening.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The cascade.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>123. EXT. DOWNTOWN INTERSECTION – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Traffic chaos after a small accident. Drivers shout at each other. Across the street Lena watches the tension grow. She says nothing this time.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The drivers begin yelling anyway. The escalation now seems self-sustaining.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>124. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – NIGHT Lena reviews city alerts on her laptop.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Multiple incidents occurring simultaneously. She smiles slightly. In her notebook she writes:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>PHASE FOUR – CASCADE CONFIRMATION.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Outside the window, Chicago buzzes with restless energy. FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>125. INT. SUBWAY PLATFORM – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Rush hour. Commuters crowd the platform waiting for the train. LENA stands near a column watching the movement patterns. Two commuters argue quietly about someone bumping into a briefcase. Lena studies them carefully but says nothing. The train arrives. The tension dissolves as the crowd moves.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She writes in her notebook:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CROWD DISPERSION LIMITS ESCALATION.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>126. INT. FINNEY'S CAR – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney sits parked near the shelter reviewing a new list of incidents.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Several have occurred without Lena being captured on camera.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're adjusting the variables.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>He circles three locations on a city map.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're building toward something.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>127. EXT. COMMUNITY BASKETBALL COURT – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A pickup basketball game draws a crowd. Lena sits on the bleachers watching players argue over fouls.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>PLAYER 1</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>That was a foul.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>PLAYER 2</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Not even close.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The tension hangs in the air.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Competition makes people personal.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The argument escalates instantly. Players shove each other before others break it up. Lena writes:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>STATUS COMPETITION – HIGH RESPONSE.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>128. INT. FINNEY'S DESK AREA – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney hasn't slept much. Coffee cups and reports clutter his desk. Jordan Park approaches with a stack of disturbance reports.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Seven new incidents overnight.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's speeding up.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney draws a circle around downtown on the map.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's concentrating them now.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>129. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Charts now cover nearly every wall. Connections between stress, crowd size, and authority presence. Lena writes:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>FINAL TEST CONDITION: PERCEIVED SYSTEM FAILURE.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>130. EXT. CITY BUS TERMINAL – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Passengers line up at several bus bays. Drivers shout departure times. Lena stands near two commuters arguing over a seat.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Travel makes people think everyone's against them.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The comment spreads through nearby passengers. Voices rise. Several people</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>start shouting. Transit police rush in before it becomes violent. Lena slips into the departing crowd.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>131. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – DINING ROOM – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Residents eat breakfast quietly. Kiara sits alone while Briggs organizes supplies. The tension between them still lingers. Lena observes but says nothing. She writes:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>LONG-TERM RESENTMENT – SLOW BURN TRIGGER.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>132. EXT. CITY OVERPASS – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Traffic crawls after a stalled vehicle blocks a lane. Drivers lean on horns.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney stands beside a patrol officer observing the chaos.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>OFFICER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>People lose their minds in traffic.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Yeah.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>And someone knows exactly how to push them there.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>133. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The wall map now highlights one large downtown district. Crowd flow lines intersect across several blocks. Lena writes a final note:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>PHASE THREE – CASCADE FAILURE EVENT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She closes the notebook slowly. Outside, the city lights stretch across the skyline. Soon the experiment will scale beyond individual fights.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>134. INT. CPD DISTRICT – BULLPEN – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The investigation wall has doubled in size. New reports stretch across the map of Chicago. Detective FINNEY studies timestamps and photos. LENA VOSS appears again and again.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Okay... now I'm starting to believe you.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's always nearby.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney circles three incidents that occurred within twenty minutes of each other.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Three different neighborhoods. Same night.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>So what is she doing?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Studying something.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>135. INT. CORPORATE OFFICE BREAK ROOM – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Office workers eat lunch quietly. LENA sits at a table with a laptop open, pretending to work remotely. Two coworkers argue softly near the coffee machine.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>COWORKER 1</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I finished that report yesterday.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>COWORKER 2</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Then why is my name on it?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena glances up casually.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Credit matters more than the work sometimes.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The tension spikes immediately. The argument escalates as Lena quietly returns to her laptop.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>136. INT. CPD DISTRICT – VIDEO REVIEW ROOM – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Surveillance footage scrolls across multiple screens. Park pauses on Lena leaving the office building.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Another one.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Yeah.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney writes the address down.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>137. INT. SUBWAY TRAIN – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Packed commuter train. Lena stands holding a rail, quietly observing passengers. Two strangers argue about someone bumping into them.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>PASSENGER 1</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Watch where you're going.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>PASSENGER 2</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Maybe don't stand in the doorway.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The argument stalls. Lena speaks without looking up.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Crowds make people territorial.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The men square up instantly. Other passengers pull them apart before punches land.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena watches, fascinated.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>138. INT. CPD DISTRICT – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney pins another photo of Lena to the board. The wall now shows incidents across bars, offices, transit, and shelters.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>It's not the places.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Then what?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>It's the people.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>139. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Charts and notes cover the desk. Her notebook now shows diagrams of human behavior loops. She writes:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>TRIGGER → RESPONSE → ESCALATION → GROUP DYNAMICS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She pauses, thinking. Then writes a new line:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>VARIABLE: OBSERVER EFFECT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>140. EXT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney watches the building again from across the street. Residents enter and leave. Lena exits the shelter with Kiara and other residents. She laughs easily, blending into the environment.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're hiding in plainsight.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>MONTAGE – VARIOUS LOCATIONS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A bar argument erupts after a comment.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Two coworkers shouting in a hallway.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A street corner confrontation.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Each time Lena appears nearby for a moment.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Each time she disappears before police arrive.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>141. INT. FINNEY'S CAR – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Photos of Lena spread across the passenger seat. Different neighborhoods. Different days. Same woman.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're not observing.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're running an experiment.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>142. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – SAME NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena reviews city incident reports on her laptop. One article mentions police investigating a pattern. She notices something in the data. Someone else has been tracking the same events. Her expression changes for the first time.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Curiosity. Then a small smile.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Interesting.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>143. INT. CPD RADIO DISPATCH – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Rows of operators field disturbance calls from across Chicago. The board lights up constantly. A SUPERVISOR studies the pattern. Across the room FINNEY watches quietly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>SUPERVISOR</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Feels like the whole city's on edge.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Someone's tightening the screws.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>144. EXT. COLLEGE CAMPUS QUAD – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Students gather between classes. LENA sits on a bench watching two debate team members arguing.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Funny how people defend ideas like territory.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Within seconds the argument becomes heated. Other students gather around. Lena notes the escalation speed.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>145. INT. FINNEY'S CAR – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney studies a new cluster of disturbances near downtown. He marks several intersections.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's compressing the timeline.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>146. INT. FITNESS CENTER LOCKER ROOM – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Athletes complain about shared equipment. Lena changes lockers quietly while listening.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>People hate unfair advantages.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Two men start arguing over a reserved machine. The tension spikes quickly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena leaves before staff intervene.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>147. INT. CPD MAP ROOM – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney overlays six days of disturbances onto a digital map. Red dots create a clear grid pattern.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>That's not random.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>No.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>That's choreography.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>148. EXT. WOMEN'S SHELTER ROOFTOP – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Kiara confronts Lena quietly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You keep showing up before people fight.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I show up everywhere.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Yeah… but you watch like you're waiting.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena says nothing. Kiara walks away uneasy.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>149. EXT. DOWNTOWN INTERSECTION – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Traffic clogs after a construction delay. Drivers shout across lanes. Lena waits at the crosswalk.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Nobody likes being slowed down.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Drivers start yelling louder. A minor fender bender sparks a larger confrontation. Lena disappears into the crowd.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>150. INT. CPD COMMAND CENTER – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney briefs a few detectives. A large downtown district glows with predicted escalation points.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's setting dominoes.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>DETECTIVE</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>For when?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Soon.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>151. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – LATE NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Her wall map is now fully connected. Lines converge across twelve blocks of downtown Chicago. She writes one final heading in her notebook.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CONVERGENCE EVENT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Below it:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>MULTI■POINT TRIGGER.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She closes the notebook slowly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Let's begin.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>152. EXT. DOWNTOWN INTERSECTION – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Commuters flood twelve blocks of downtown Chicago.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Coffee lines, buses, construction delays, street vendors. Everything normal — but tense. Across the street, FINNEY scans the crowds.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's already here somewhere.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>153. EXT. MULTIPLE DOWNTOWN LOCATIONS – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena moves through the district making small passing remarks to strangers.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>One about cutting lines. Another about disrespect. Another about cheating someone. Tiny sparks across the district.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>154. EXT. DOWNTOWN BLOCK – LATE MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>One argument erupts between drivers. Two blocks away a café argument spills into the street. Across the district a construction dispute escalates. Police radios begin lighting up.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>155. INT. CPD COMMAND CENTER – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Screens show live feeds of disturbances across downtown. Calls flood the dispatch system. Finney studies the chaos.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>This is it. The cascade.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>We can't stop all of them.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>We don't have to.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>We stop her.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>156. EXT. ROOFTOP OVERLOOK – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena watches the city erupt below. Sirens echo across the district.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Arguments everywhere. Small fights breaking out across several blocks.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She writes calmly in her notebook.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>RESULT: SYSTEM OVERLOAD.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>157. INT. FINNEY'S CAR – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney studies surveillance footage overnight.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>He notices a pattern of Lena's movements across cameras.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You always stop to watch the center of the reaction.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>158. EXT. DOWNTOWN PARK – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney waits near the center of the convergence zone. Lena appears exactly where he predicted.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Experiment's over.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You can't end human nature, Detective.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>159. EXT. CITY STREET – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Crowds still tense after days of disturbances. Finney walks beside Lena.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You proved your theory.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Now people are getting hurt.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>People were already hurting each other. I just revealed it.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>160. INT. LOCAL NEWS STUDIO – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Anchors discuss the wave of disturbances. Officials claim police restored order. Finney watches the broadcast from a diner counter.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Order wasn't restored.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>It just burned itself out.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>161. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – LATE NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Her wall map shows the completed cascade pattern. She writes one final note beneath it.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINAL VARIABLE:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>DETECTIVE RESPONSE.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She underlines the words twice.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Let's see what you do next.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>162. EXT. DOWNTOWN STREET – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A news van broadcasts live coverage of the rising disturbances. Reporters speculate about social tension spreading across the city. Across the street, Lena watches the broadcast quietly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Awareness accelerates reaction.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>163. INT. FINNEY'S CAR – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney studies the downtown grid again. Twelve blocks circled in red.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's building pressure.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>And when it breaks… it breaks everywhere.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>164. INT. DOWNTOWN CAFÉ – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Office workers crowd the café. Lena sits alone with coffee. Two coworkers argue about deadlines.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>People hate when someone makes them look incompetent. The argument erupts immediately. Customers begin shouting across tables. Managers intervene.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>165. INT. CPD ANALYSIS ROOM – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney overlays the newest disturbances onto the city grid. The pattern now forms a ring around the convergence zone.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JORDAN PARK</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's closing the circle.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Yeah.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The center is next.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>166. INT. BUS PLATFORM – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Crowds push through evening commuters. Lena whispers to a frustrated passenger.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Nobody respects anyone anymore.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Within seconds several commuters argue. Security whistles blow. The tension spreads down the platform.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>167. EXT. DOWNTOWN BLOCK – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney interviews witnesses after the disturbance. He looks up at the surrounding streets.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She's priming them.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>168. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Residents watch a TV news report about the city disturbances. Kiara studies Lena carefully.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Every time something happens… you're nearby.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena meets her eyes calmly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Maybe I'm just observant.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>169. EXT. PUBLIC PARK FESTIVAL – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A neighborhood festival fills the park. Lena walks through the crowd making brief comments to strangers. Arguments ignite in several small pockets.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Police begin arriving to calm the crowd. Across the park Finney spots her.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Not this time.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>He pushes through the crowd — but she's gone again.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>170. EXT. DOWNTOWN OVERLOOK – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena stands above the convergence zone. Traffic, nightlife, and commuters fill the streets below. Her notebook rests open.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She writes:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CONVERGENCE TRIGGER – READY.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Below it:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>MULTI-POINT ACTIVATION – TOMORROW.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Let's see what happens when everything ignites at once.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>171. INT. CPD DISTRICT – CAPTAIN THOMAS' OFFICE – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Captain Thomas slams a folder of reports on the desk.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CAPTAIN THOMAS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Forty-three disturbances in four days. The mayor's office is calling this a public safety crisis.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney stands his ground.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>It's one person.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CAPTAIN THOMAS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Then prove it or drop it.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>172. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena studies a new page titled:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CRITICAL THRESHOLD.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Under it she writes:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>HIGH STRESS + FEAR + GROUP REACTION</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She circles the word FEAR.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>173. INT. MAJOR TRAIN TERMINAL – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Thousands of commuters move through the terminal. Finney scans the massive crowd. He knows Lena will choose somewhere chaotic.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>174. INT. TERMINAL FOOD COURT – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena stands near a crowded seating area. Two travelers argue about someone taking a chair. Security nearby watches but doesn't intervene. The tension is rising but still contained.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Funny how people panic when they think something's been taken from them.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>One traveler shouts.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>TRAVELER 1</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You think I'm stealing your seat?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Chairs scrape. Voices rise.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>175. INT. TERMINAL FLOOR – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The argument spreads through nearby tables. Another traveler jumps in.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Suddenly multiple arguments break out at once. Security whistles blow.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>176. INT. TERMINAL FOOD COURT – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney reaches Lena before the situation explodes.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>That's enough.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena studies him calmly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You stopped it earlier than expected.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're done.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>No.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're learning.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>177. INT. TERMINAL EXIT – MOMENTS LATER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Security and police break up the arguments. Finney and Lena stand away from the crowd.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're creating chaos just to watch it.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>No.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I'm proving something.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>What?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>That civilization is thinner than people think.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>178. EXT. TRAIN TERMINAL – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Commuters pour onto the city streets. Police lights flash in the distance.  Lena walks away into the crowd again. Finney watches her disappear. This time he doesn't look frustrated. He looks determined.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Game on.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>179. INT. LATE NIGHT DINER – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney sits alone at the counter finishing coffee. A TV reports on the downtown cascade disturbances. Customers argue quietly about the news.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney watches them carefully now — studying reactions the way Lena does.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're right... it doesn't take much.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>180. EXT. CITY SIDE STREET – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena walks past two delivery drivers arguing over a parking spot. She says nothing. The drivers begin shouting anyway. The system now reacts without direct input.She writes:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>SELF-SUSTAINING ESCALATION.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>181. INT. CPD TRAINING ROOM – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney speaks with several officers about the disturbances.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>OFFICER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You think one person caused all that?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>No.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She just showed everyone how easy it is.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>182. EXT. DOWNTOWN CROSSWALK – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena deliberately walks past Finney on a busy street. She doesn't stop — just one quiet line as she passes.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Still studying behavior, Detective?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney turns but she's already disappearing into the crowd.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>183. EXT. CITY PARK – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney waits on a bench, knowing she'll appear eventually. Lena approaches calmly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You predicted the location.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You predicted my response.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>They sit across from each other like chess players.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>184. INT. PUBLIC LIBRARY – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena observes people working quietly. Two students whisper angrily about a shared project.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Collaboration reveals resentment.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The argument escalates before a librarian intervenes.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>185. INT. FINNEY'S CAR – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney watches Lena exit the library. He doesn't follow immediately. Instead he writes something in his notebook.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>COUNTER-EXPERIMENT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>186. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Kiara approaches Finney quietly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You think she's causing those fights.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You noticed too.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She watches people like they're puzzles.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney nods. Confirmation.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>187. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – MIDNIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Her wall map is complete. The cascade experiment is finished. She writes the next phase in her notebook.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINAL EXPERIMENT – DETECTIVE TRIGGER.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She closes the book slowly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Let's see what you do when you're the variable.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>188. EXT. CITY COURTHOUSE STEPS – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Crowds gather for multiple hearings. Lawyers, defendants, reporters. FINNEY watches the movement of people carefully. He’s no longer just investigating — he’s anticipating behavior.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're going to try to make me the spark.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>189. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena studies surveillance photos of Finney.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A new notebook page reads:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>DETECTIVE RESPONSE PATTERNS.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She circles three triggers:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>INJUSTICE – PROTECTION – AUTHORITY.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Everyone has a pressure point.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>190. INT. SUBWAY TRAIN – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Passengers packed tightly into the car. Lena observes Finney standing across from her. Two passengers argue about space. Lena watches Finney carefully — waiting.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>PASSENGER</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Move over, man.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney calmly separates them before escalation.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena writes:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>RESPONSE – DE-ESCALATION.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>191. EXT. STREET MARKET – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Crowds move between vendors. Lena whispers something to a vendor accusing another of cheating.The vendor confronts a customer aggressively. Finney intervenes again, calming the situation.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're predictable, Detective.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>So are you.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>192. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Kiara argues with Walter Briggs in the hallway. The tension escalates quickly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena watches silently from the doorway. Finney arrives just in time to break the argument apart.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>This ends tonight.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>193. INT. PARKING STRUCTURE – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney confronts Lena directly in an empty structure. City noise echoes in the distance.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You want me to trigger something.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I want to see what happens when the system's protector breaks it.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>I'm not part of your experiment.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You already are.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>194. EXT. DOWNTOWN PLAZA – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Hundreds of people move through the plaza during a large event. Lena stands across the square watching Finney in the crowd. Everything is ready for the final test. Finney notices her watching him. They lock eyes across the crowd.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Your move.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>195. EXT. DOWNTOWN PLAZA – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Workers dismantle event tents from the previous night. FINNEY walks the plaza studying entrances, exits, crowd flow. He’s mapping Lena’s potential triggers.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>If I were you… where would I start the fire?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>196. INT. COFFEE SHOP OVERLOOKING PLAZA – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>LENA watches Finney through the window below. Her notebook open:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINAL EXPERIMENT – DETECTIVE RESPONSE.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You're learning the rules of the game.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>197. EXT. CITY BUS STOP – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Passengers argue about a delayed bus. Lena stands nearby but says nothing.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney arrives and calmly diffuses the argument. Lena observes carefully.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Still resisting the trigger.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>198. EXT. STREET PROTEST – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A political protest fills several downtown blocks. Crowds chant loudly. Police lines hold the perimeter. Lena moves through the crowd whispering comments to</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>different groups. Tension rises rapidly. Finney spots her in the crowd.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Not today.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>199. EXT. PROTEST CENTER – CONTINUOUS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Two protesters shove each other. A bottle flies. Crowd tension spikes. Lena watches Finney closely. If Finney overreacts — the crowd could explode.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>This is the moment, Detective.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney raises his hands calmly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Everyone take a breath.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Nobody moves.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The crowd hesitates.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The escalation stalls.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>200. EXT. CITY ROOFTOP – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Lena stands overlooking the calm city.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Her notebook open. She writes:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINAL RESULT – CONTROLLED RESPONSE.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She pauses, thinking.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Interesting.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Across the street, Finney watches her from another rooftop.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Experiment's over.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>201. EXT. DOWNTOWN PLAZA – MORNING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The plaza is quiet again. Workers clean up protest debris and remove barricades.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>FINNEY walks through the space where the crowd nearly ignited days earlier.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Life has returned to normal — at least on the surface.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>People move on fast.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>202. INT. CPD CAPTAIN THOMAS' OFFICE – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Captain Thomas reads a stack of incident summaries.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CAPTAIN THOMAS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>City says disturbances are down.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>They burned themselves out.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CAPTAIN THOMAS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You ever prove that theory of yours?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney hesitates.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Not the way you'd want in a report.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>203. INT. WOMEN'S SHELTER – AFTERNOON</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Residents eat lunch together. Kiara watches Lena from across the room. Lena sits quietly reading a book, calm as ever.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>KIARA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>It's been quiet lately.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Systems stabilize eventually.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Kiara doesn't fully trust her — but says nothing.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>204. EXT. RIVERWALK – EVENING</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney walks beside Lena along the river. The city skyline glows behind them.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You got what you wanted.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Data.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>People got hurt.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>People were already hurting each other.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>You just proved something interesting.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>What's that?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The system works when someone chooses restraint.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>205. INT. LENA'S APARTMENT – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Her wall map is gone. Only a single notebook remains on the desk.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She writes one last entry.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINAL NOTE:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>VARIABLE — HUMAN CHOICE.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>She closes the notebook slowly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>CUT TO:</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>206. EXT. CITY OVERLOOK – SUNSET</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Finney stands above the city watching traffic move through the streets.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>People arguing, laughing, living. All the normal friction of a big city.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Behind him Lena approaches quietly.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>LENA</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Still studying behavior, Detective?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>No.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FINNEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Just hoping people choose better.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>They look out over Chicago together — the city still alive with unpredictable human nature.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>FADE OUT.</Text></Paragraph>
  </Content>
</FinalDraft>
